Deal.

286
00:18:57,320 --> 00:18:58,080
We’ll see.

287
00:19:09,440 --> 00:19:10,560
Nai.

288
00:19:16,040 --> 00:19:19,200
Sorry, the number you are calling…

289
00:19:54,160 --> 00:19:55,560
P’Earth krap.

290
00:20:03,360 --> 00:20:05,480
I have a drink for you.

291
00:20:06,800 --> 00:20:09,720
I walked pass the beverage stall so I bought it.

292
00:20:12,200 --> 00:20:15,640
I just walked pass the beverage stall too.

293
00:20:17,520 --> 00:20:18,840
Okay

294
00:20:26,000 --> 00:20:27,320
Here you go.

295
00:20:29,320 --> 00:20:30,680
Thank you.

296
00:20:36,960 --> 00:20:39,040
We will be full by these.

297
00:20:40,200 --> 00:20:41,960
We have two of this.

298
00:20:56,520 --> 00:20:58,520
Put it on my desk, Cherry.

299
00:20:58,840 --> 00:21:00,200
I’ll sign it later.

300
00:21:56,160 --> 00:21:57,480
I have been looking for you.

301
00:21:57,720 --> 00:21:59,080
Where have you been?

302
00:22:00,120 --> 00:22:02,600
I’m here to get your signature for my document

303
00:22:03,200 --> 00:22:05,840
Well, I have been to…

304
00:22:08,720 --> 00:22:10,440
find something to eat.

305
00:22:14,440 --> 00:22:16,560
You want me to sign your document?

306
00:22:17,640 --> 00:22:18,920
Give it to me.

307
00:22:33,080 --> 00:22:34,080
Here.

308
00:22:34,520 --> 00:22:35,760
Thank you.

309
00:22:40,240 --> 00:22:41,120
Now that you get the document

310
00:22:41,320 --> 00:22:42,520
what’s your plan?

311
00:22:45,640 --> 00:22:47,320
Well, I think I go home.

312
00:22:53,240 --> 00:22:54,920
Can I give you a lift?

313
00:22:58,440 --> 00:23:02,000
My home is in Chiangmai.

314
00:23:22,400 --> 00:23:24,400
Well I’m taking off first.

315
00:23:24,640 --> 00:23:25,560
Sawasdee krap.

316
00:23:25,680 --> 00:23:26,560
See you, Tod.

317
00:23:37,680 --> 00:23:39,480
P’Durian krap!

318
00:23:40,360 --> 00:23:41,640
Nong Arthit?

319
00:23:42,200 --> 00:23:43,440
What are you doing?

320
00:23:44,080 --> 00:23:45,640
You scared the life out of me.

321
00:23:46,200 --> 00:23:49,720
I’m here to get the document for Kongpob

322
00:23:49,880 --> 00:23:52,160
Okay, give me a sec.

323
00:23:52,320 --> 00:23:54,480
What’s the rush?

324
00:23:54,680 --> 00:23:57,320
It’s a secret.

325
00:23:59,240 --> 00:24:01,160
Always a secret.

326
00:24:01,600 --> 00:24:02,800
Here you are.

327
00:24:06,320 --> 00:24:07,320
Thank you

328
00:24:07,760 --> 00:24:08,280
You’re welcome.

329
00:24:28,520 --> 00:24:31,360
Seeing this reminds me of us in the first year

330
00:24:31,520 --> 00:24:32,520
Yes.

331
00:24:32,680 --> 00:24:34,080
Very much.

332
00:24:47,240 --> 00:24:48,520
Hey, where are you going?

333
00:24:49,280 --> 00:24:50,680
Watch them.

334
00:24:51,000 --> 00:24:52,640
Though we are the fourth-year seniors.

335
00:24:52,880 --> 00:24:54,640
They are our juniors.

336
00:24:54,960 --> 00:24:57,080
It’s our duty to looking out for them.

337
00:24:57,240 --> 00:24:59,160
Who wants to come with me?

338
00:25:02,200 --> 00:25:03,200
Great.

339
00:25:03,400 --> 00:25:05,560
No wonder why you were the head hazer

340
00:25:05,840 --> 00:25:07,000
Let’s go.

341
00:25:07,120 --> 00:25:07,720
No.

342
00:25:07,800 --> 00:25:08,480
I have an appointment

343
00:25:08,720 --> 00:25:09,880
See you later.

344
00:25:12,840 --> 00:25:15,680
Ah, you are coming with me?

345
00:25:15,760 --> 00:25:16,960
I know you want to.

346
00:25:18,040 --> 00:25:19,600
May, come on.

347
00:25:19,800 --> 00:25:20,840
Let’s get going, May.

348
00:25:21,320 --> 00:25:23,560
Well, we are going to have dinner with May’s family.

349
00:25:25,960 --> 00:25:27,320
See you later.

350
00:25:27,400 --> 00:25:28,760
Really?

351
00:25:32,160 --> 00:25:33,920
Okay, Maprang.

352
00:25:34,040 --> 00:25:35,160
You are coming with me.

353
00:25:35,320 --> 00:25:36,160
Let’s go.

354
00:25:36,240 --> 00:25:37,200
Are you crazy?

355
00:25:37,320 --> 00:25:38,360
We are not hazers anymore

356
00:25:38,840 --> 00:25:40,000
You go there alone.

357
00:25:41,160 --> 00:25:42,040
See you.

358
00:25:44,360 --> 00:25:46,200
Prae, come with me.

359
00:25:46,840 --> 00:25:48,080
Honey.

360
00:25:52,320 --> 00:25:53,920
I have her answer.

361
00:25:55,680 --> 00:25:57,120
Miss you so much.

362
00:25:58,280 --> 00:25:59,440
All right, Tew

363
00:25:59,680 --> 00:26:00,680
You are the only one left.

364
00:26:00,760 --> 00:26:01,680
Let’s go.

365
00:26:03,160 --> 00:26:04,160
So sorry.

366
00:26:04,280 --> 00:26:05,720
I have a date.

367
00:26:05,920 --> 00:26:07,080
I go with you next time.

368
00:26:07,200 --> 00:26:08,320
See you.

369
00:26:09,880 --> 00:26:11,760
You all are gone?

370
00:26:24,400 --> 00:26:25,680
Fine!

371
00:26:38,720 --> 00:26:39,440
Everyone,

372
00:26:39,720 --> 00:26:41,160
raise your drink.

373
00:26:41,520 --> 00:26:43,920
Cheers to the freedom of me.

374
00:26:49,240 --> 00:26:50,920
Let me introduce

375
00:26:51,120 --> 00:26:52,680
my girlfriend.

376
00:26:52,880 --> 00:26:54,200
Her name is Tob.

377
00:26:54,280 --> 00:26:56,400
Tob, nice to meet you.

378
00:26:56,560 --> 00:26:58,240
Nice to meet you too.

379
00:27:02,600 --> 00:27:06,560
Guys, I need to go now.

380
00:27:06,720 --> 00:27:07,760
Wait.

381
00:27:07,880 --> 00:27:09,480
I just got out of the military service.

382
00:27:09,600 --> 00:27:11,320
Why are you rushing?

383
00:27:12,400 --> 00:27:13,320
I really have to go.

384
00:27:13,560 --> 00:27:14,880
Where are you going?

385
00:27:15,480 --> 00:27:16,720
Tell us.

386
00:27:17,280 --> 00:27:18,200
It’s a secret.

387
00:27:18,320 --> 00:27:19,920
What secret?

388
00:27:20,120 --> 00:27:22,800
You can look at his picture. I put it right here

389
00:27:25,600 --> 00:27:27,280
Where’s the stuff I ordered?

390
00:27:33,840 --> 00:27:34,320
Wonderful.

391
00:27:34,560 --> 00:27:36,160
What did you just give him?

392
00:27:37,040 --> 00:27:37,920
What is it?

393
00:27:37,960 --> 00:27:39,000
It’s not ectasy!

394
00:27:39,120 --> 00:27:39,720
I’m going.

395
00:27:39,800 --> 00:27:40,760
Bye

396
00:27:44,040 --> 00:27:45,640
Nice to meet you, Tob.

397
00:27:53,800 --> 00:27:55,880
Let me help.

398
00:28:01,520 --> 00:28:02,920
Water for you.

399
00:28:03,920 --> 00:28:04,360
Thanks.

400
00:28:04,440 --> 00:28:05,760
What about these snacks?

401
00:28:05,800 --> 00:28:07,440
Do you want to put them here or on the front?

402
00:28:07,600 --> 00:28:09,160
Let’s put them on the front.

403
00:28:10,480 --> 00:28:12,840
The football match is about to start.

404
00:28:18,400 --> 00:28:19,280
Trust me.

405
00:28:19,640 --> 00:28:22,320
Liverpool will win tonight.

406
00:28:23,320 --> 00:28:24,320
P’Yong.

407
00:28:25,080 --> 00:28:26,240
Last time

408
00:28:26,720 --> 00:28:28,120
you still owe me a meal.

409
00:28:28,280 --> 00:28:30,040
If Liverpool loses again,

410
00:28:30,520 --> 00:28:32,840
you will have to stay in Chiangmai and buy me

411
00:28:33,360 --> 00:28:35,400
If Liverpool wins,

412
00:28:35,720 --> 00:28:36,720
we are even.

413
00:28:38,280 --> 00:28:39,200
No, we are not.

414
00:28:39,680 --> 00:28:41,600
We both owe each other a meal.

415
00:28:42,480 --> 00:28:45,600
You really want me to buy you a meal, Right?

416
00:28:46,680 --> 00:28:47,680
Well,

417
00:28:47,800 --> 00:28:50,240
you break the agreement of a meal bet.

418
00:28:50,680 --> 00:28:52,760
I don’t even ask for penalty fee of that yet.

419
00:28:53,160 --> 00:28:54,840
You want to charge me the penalty fee too?

420
00:28:55,200 --> 00:28:56,480
How can you be so bloody canny?

421
00:28:57,560 --> 00:28:58,960
You don’t have to pay for the fare.

422
00:28:59,360 --> 00:29:01,080
You don’t have to pay for the fuel even.

423
00:29:01,480 --> 00:29:03,760
Also these snacks.

424
00:29:11,840 --> 00:29:16,480
Well, I take you to a good place of Khao Soi in Chiangmai then

425
00:29:16,800 --> 00:29:17,760
Okay?

426
00:29:19,080 --> 00:29:20,080
Fine.

427
00:29:20,240 --> 00:29:22,040
I hope it’s good like you said

428
00:29:23,840 --> 00:29:26,280
Khao Soi in Chiangmai is definitely good

429
00:29:27,240 --> 00:29:28,480
Let’s go

430
00:29:30,480 --> 00:29:32,640
You talk like you are the driver.

431
00:29:58,400 --> 00:30:00,000
Please give us a sec

432
00:30:42,240 --> 00:30:43,440
Kongpob.

433
00:30:46,400 --> 00:30:48,120
Have I kept you waiting for so long?

434
00:30:49,440 --> 00:30:50,360
No.

435
00:30:50,560 --> 00:30:51,640
I have just got here

436
00:30:54,520 --> 00:30:56,640
Why do you want to see me here?

437
00:30:59,960 --> 00:31:01,720
I have something for you

438
00:31:08,800 --> 00:31:10,000
Here.

439
00:31:16,040 --> 00:31:17,040
Thank you

440
00:31:17,280 --> 00:31:18,840
for getting the internship certification for me

441
00:31:20,400 --> 00:31:22,640
The thing I actually want to give you

442
00:31:23,680 --> 00:31:25,040
is this

443
00:31:29,160 --> 00:31:30,640
Excited, right?

444
00:32:02,840 --> 00:32:04,160
From now on,

445
00:32:05,120 --> 00:32:07,720
These gears don’t just represent us each anymore

446
00:32:10,640 --> 00:32:13,120
Our hearts are now merged together in each of them

447
00:32:18,760 --> 00:32:20,000
Kongpob,

448
00:32:21,880 --> 00:32:23,560
I want to ask you one thing.

449
00:32:30,440 --> 00:32:33,560
Are you ready for our future?

450
00:32:40,520 --> 00:32:41,600
What about you, P’Arthit?

451
00:32:41,840 --> 00:32:43,160
Are you ready for it?

452
00:33:17,800 --> 00:33:19,920
The weather is hot, right?

453
00:33:20,320 --> 00:33:21,880
Kongpob,

454
00:33:25,120 --> 00:33:27,040
the pen you gave me,

455
00:33:28,200 --> 00:33:29,760
the ink doesn’t come off.

456
00:33:30,320 --> 00:33:32,360
I dipped it in the hot water

457
00:33:32,480 --> 00:33:33,800
It’s still not working

458
00:33:38,000 --> 00:33:39,320
Let me see

459
00:33:52,920 --> 00:33:54,080
It’s impossible for the ink to come out.

460
00:33:54,920 --> 00:33:56,120
The ink is empty.

461
00:33:58,520 --> 00:33:59,560
Really?

462
00:34:00,480 --> 00:34:02,040
It’s empty?

463
00:34:03,840 --> 00:34:06,880
So you use it a lot.

464
00:34:09,320 --> 00:34:12,320
Well, I make the most out of everything I use

465
00:34:16,400 --> 00:34:18,080
Do you make the most out of me too?

466
00:34:20,080 --> 00:34:21,280
Very funny.

467
00:34:26,200 --> 00:34:28,040
Shall we go back now?

468
00:34:30,520 --> 00:34:33,320
Can I enjoy the atmosphere here for a little longer?

469
00:34:58,160 --> 00:35:00,880
Directed by
Padung Smajarn / Pongpisit Botsri

470
00:35:07,360 --> 00:35:08,840
Sorry, P’Arthit.

471
00:35:09,000 --> 00:35:10,280
It’s your day off.

472
00:35:10,400 --> 00:35:11,600
But I bother you to help get my stuff

473
00:35:11,640 --> 00:35:13,040
and take pictures in the campus.

474
00:35:13,120 --> 00:35:14,200
It’s okay.

475
00:35:14,280 --> 00:35:16,000
It’s been a while since I came back here.

476
00:35:16,520 --> 00:35:20,360
But it still makes me feel the same.

477
00:35:20,680 --> 00:35:23,040
It’s still the place I feel good

478
00:35:25,080 --> 00:35:26,960
when I have you around. I guess.

479
00:35:28,320 --> 00:35:30,280
I guess so.

480
00:35:30,480 --> 00:35:32,240
Shall we go now?

481
00:35:32,400 --> 00:35:33,960
We still have to get back here to get your stuff.

482
00:35:34,360 --> 00:35:35,600
Okay.

483
00:36:02,360 --> 00:36:05,080
♬ How good has this been ♬

484
00:36:05,400 --> 00:36:09,800
♬ …that we love and care ♬

485
00:36:10,040 --> 00:36:14,840
♬ and have been through many things together? ♬

486
00:36:15,800 --> 00:36:18,240
♬ This is love ♬

487
00:36:18,520 --> 00:36:21,680
♬ The love I do not expect anyone to understand ♬

488
00:36:21,920 --> 00:36:24,520
♬ Just you and me ♬

489
00:36:24,760 --> 00:36:25,560
Sorry.

490
00:36:25,720 --> 00:36:27,000
Hi, P’Kongpob. P’Arthit.

491
00:36:27,080 --> 00:36:28,120
Sawasdee krap.

492
00:36:28,280 --> 00:36:29,440
want to join ?

493
00:36:29,600 --> 00:36:31,160
It's okay.

494
00:36:31,840 --> 00:36:33,400
We are here to take some pictures.

495
00:36:33,560 --> 00:36:34,400
Hey, guys.

496
00:36:34,520 --> 00:36:36,400
P’Kong has graduated.

497
00:36:36,560 --> 00:36:37,720
Let’s take a picture with him.

498
00:36:37,920 --> 00:36:38,480
Well,

499
00:36:38,680 --> 00:36:39,600
excuse me, then.

500
00:36:57,760 --> 00:36:59,480
Who are you looking for?

501
00:37:00,400 --> 00:37:01,640
P’Arthit,

502
00:37:02,240 --> 00:37:03,600
I’m sorry.

503
00:37:03,920 --> 00:37:05,440
For what?

504
00:37:05,720 --> 00:37:07,800
You just took a picture with them.

505
00:37:09,720 --> 00:37:10,680
Here.

506
00:37:11,040 --> 00:37:13,400
I have this ice cream for you.

507
00:37:14,640 --> 00:37:15,600
2 flavors,

508
00:37:15,840 --> 00:37:17,600
Chocolate or strawberry

509
00:37:19,520 --> 00:37:21,800
Can I choose that flavor?

510
00:37:25,640 --> 00:37:27,880
No?

511
00:37:28,760 --> 00:37:30,680
I have Chocolate, then.

512
00:37:46,840 --> 00:37:48,280
It’s good, right?

513
00:37:51,680 --> 00:37:53,000
What are you doing?

514
00:37:53,040 --> 00:37:54,280
Just stay still.

515
00:38:05,640 --> 00:38:07,240
It’s sweet

516
00:38:08,400 --> 00:38:09,920
and soft.

517
00:38:10,880 --> 00:38:12,400
It’s just chocolate.

518
00:38:12,560 --> 00:38:13,880
Not that sweet and soft

519
00:38:16,440 --> 00:38:17,800
I mean...

520
00:38:19,400 --> 00:38:20,720
your lips.

521
00:38:21,000 --> 00:38:22,960
It’s so sweet that I almost melt.

522
00:38:25,160 --> 00:38:26,720
Can I taste them?

523
00:38:28,240 --> 00:38:29,960
What are you talking about?

524
00:38:31,040 --> 00:38:32,880
Let’s go now.

525
00:38:33,360 --> 00:38:35,320
You still have to get your stuff, don’t you?

526
00:38:46,080 --> 00:38:46,720
Sorry, Kongpob.

527
00:38:46,880 --> 00:38:48,440
Let me get them.

528
00:38:56,840 --> 00:38:57,560
Hey, Kongpob.

529
00:38:58,240 --> 00:38:59,280
Do you still keep these things?

530
00:38:59,440 --> 00:39:01,000
I keep everything

531
00:39:01,240 --> 00:39:04,720
They are all my memories of you and me

532
00:39:06,120 --> 00:39:07,840
Always over the top.

533
00:39:09,560 --> 00:39:10,600
Why?

534
00:39:10,960 --> 00:39:14,880
You also keep my cards and gifts in your room

535
00:39:22,720 --> 00:39:23,720
Finally.

536
00:39:25,800 --> 00:39:27,120
What are you doing next?

537
00:39:27,680 --> 00:39:29,360
I’m waiting to hear the result of my interview

538
00:39:29,880 --> 00:39:32,560
But I’m not sure if I really want to go there yet

539
00:39:33,600 --> 00:39:35,080
You have to promise me.

540
00:39:35,480 --> 00:39:36,720
If you pass the interview,

541
00:39:37,000 --> 00:39:39,200
you wouldn’t let this opportunity go.

542
00:39:39,520 --> 00:39:41,320
Are you sure

543
00:39:41,520 --> 00:39:43,280
that you can be alone.

544
00:39:43,600 --> 00:39:45,280
Remember that time?

545
00:39:45,400 --> 00:39:48,280
I went to Japan with my family 2 weeks

546
00:39:48,480 --> 00:39:50,720
You were so lonely that you wanted me to stay over at your place

547
00:39:50,840 --> 00:39:51,480
Don’t be ridiculous

548
00:39:51,880 --> 00:39:54,200
It was you who asked for staying over

549
00:39:54,880 --> 00:39:56,520
P’Arthit krap.

550
00:39:57,640 --> 00:39:58,960
If you are lonely,

551
00:39:59,560 --> 00:40:01,440
you can say it to me directly.

552
00:40:02,760 --> 00:40:03,840
How about

553
00:40:06,640 --> 00:40:07,520
we do something tonight

554
00:40:07,680 --> 00:40:09,640
so you won’t get lonely?

555
00:40:09,800 --> 00:40:11,160
Kongpob!

556
00:40:12,440 --> 00:40:14,000
Pull this up.

557
00:40:20,000 --> 00:40:21,000
Wrong side.

558
00:40:58,040 --> 00:41:06,040
“What makes you think I’m following you.
I want to walk along with you.” – Arthit
